@NikolajBjorner Thanks. Is there also a corresponding changes to the python/Makefile build system. I did a quick skim of this very large PR and I couldn't see it. We should keep the build systems in sync.

Requiring a C++11 capable compiler is a breaking change. AFAIK this hasn't been required up until now. I have no problem with this requirement because most modern C++ compilers support C++11.

I do worry if such a change would break existing code. For example will the introduction of C++11's implicit move constructors silently break existing code?

